snippet.textDisplay: Tropic Thunder was not blackface. Blackface was an offensive clown-like minstrel show performance making a mockery of black people during a time of systemic & societal-norm racism. Know the difference. Stop making parallels. Check your "victimhood" if you think Tropic Thunder was 'offensive'. If Tropic Thunder was offensive, then White Chicks was offensive. If you believe Tropic Thunder was 'punching down' and White Chicks is OK because it's 'punching up' ... then you are a racist ... because YOU are (at your core) actually holding an ideology that black people are lower than white people on some kind of value scale. Thus you don't believe races are equal in value. Racist. Because if in accepted context races are equal, Tropic Thunder and White Chicks contain nothing racially offensive. It literally takes being a racist to find these movies racist. Amazing paradox. Meanwhile, in the minds of the offended, they feel they are correct, good, virtuous, and woke. All while deep in their spines, they harbour a racial value hierarchy with whites higher and blacks lower. Yikes. Not so woke, is it.
